-- Euro Rises After ECB 3-Month Loan Demand From Banks Is Less Than Expected
-- Daniel Tilles
-- 2010-06-30T09:20:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/euro-rises-after-ecb-3-month-loan-demand-from-banks-is-less-than-expected.html

          
          
             The euro extended gains after
lenders asked the European Central Bank for 131.9 billion euros
($161.8 billion) of three-month loans, before a 12-month
facility is repaid tomorrow.  
 The euro climbed 0.6 percent to $1.2264 as of 10:19 a.m. in
London.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
